{"/service/ndnp/au/batch_au_inman_ver01/data/sn85038485/00340582603/1913111601/0287.xml":{"full_text":"QUOTATION LEVEL\nUFTED AGAIN BY\nBUYING MOVEMENT\nLondon Leads in Buying as\nResult of More Favorable\nMexican Outlook\nGENERAL TRADERS\nARE STILL SULLEN\nFeel That They Are Unwilling to\nTake Much Risk Unless\nThings Assume a More\nSettled Aspect\nBy W. G. NICHOLAS\nNew York, November IB\u2014(Special)\u2014The\nlevel of quotations was lifted moderately\nthis week and revival of bullish senti\nment was proclaimed. Activity was con\nk tentrated upon the old group of half\ndozen favorites, reinforced by a handful\nof specialties. By common consent Lon\ndon was given credit for leading tho\nbuying, being moved thereto by the al\nleged -subsidence of Mexican belligerency,\nand also by the bright prospect of cur\nrency legislation during the life of the\nspecial session of Congress.\nThe reasoning that resulted from the\nunexpected allowance of <6,000,000 addi\ntional wages for account of trainmen and\nconductors, was that the Interstate com\nmerce commission would be shown there\nby the imperative last straw necessity\nof allowing the railroads an offsetting\n<60,000,000 freight rate raise. It could not\nbe delected that the public went wild\nover the developments of the week, but\nsome definite improvement was claimed\nby the fullishly Inclined traders, and\nsymptoms of public enlistment on the\nbuying side was observed at intervals.\nSporadic activity was made the most of\nto arouse public Interest, but strange as\nit may seem, an overwhellng majority of\nbankers and brokers still advise their\nfriends and customers to \"keep out of the\nmarket\u201d until \"conditions take definite\nform.\u201d\nAsked for a bill of particulars, or some\n\"definite\u201d Information, tba wise men con\nfess they are helpless as children; in\ndesperation they stick to the above\n11 noted phrase There Is nothing to take\nUs place thus flir. The limit of prices\n.ms been narrow throughout the entire\nlist and except for an occasional little\nrally signalizing usually the \"run.ilng\nin,\u201d of a group of timid bears, the play\nwas featureless. Mexico furnished near\nest approach to fireworks. The keenest\namong the students and professional\nHauers confess frankly that they do not\nknow whether the market Is \"over\nbought\" or \"over-sold,\" and cannot find\nout. The expression Is well nigh unan\nimous from the traders\u2019 standpoint that\nthe situation is still u hopeless mystery,\n1..\"\nPILES\nQuickly\nCured\nInstant Relief, Permanent Cure\u2014Trial\nPackage Mailed Free to All\nIn Plain Wrapper\nWe want every man and woman, suf\n/\u00a9ring from the excruciating torture of\nl piles to just send their name and ad\ndress to us and get, by return mail, a\nfree trial package of the most effective\nand positive cure ever known for this\nI disease. Pyramid Pile Remedy.\nThe way to prove what this great rem\ni rdy will do in your own case, is to just\nlill out free coupon and sent to us and\nyou will get by return mail a free sample\nof Pyramid Pile Remedy.\nThen, after you have proven to yourself\nwhat it can do, you will go to the drug\ngist and get a 60-cent box.\nDon\u2019t undergo an operation. Operations\ni are rarely a success and often lead to\nterrible consequences. Pyramid Pile Rem\nedy reduoeR all inflammation, makes con\njw Kestion, irritation, itching, soreR and ul\ni cers disappear\u2014and the piles simply quit.\nFor sale at all drug stores at BO cents\nI a box.\nFree Package Coupon\ni Fill out the blank lines below with\nI\" your name and address, cut out cou\npon and mall to the PYRAMID\nDRUG CO., A0\u00ab Pyramid Rids., Mar\ni shall, Mich. A trial package of the\ngreat Pyramid Pile Remedy will\nthen be sent you at onco by mall,\nFREE, In plain wrapper.\nI\nlb Name\nft Street\ncity. State\ni\ni _\nKING ALFONSO WOULD\nFIGHT FOR REPUBLIC\nw *c/M?wsavso x///.\nKing Alfonso is reported to have said\nrecently:\u2014\n\u201cIty lore of Spain Is sucii that if a\nrepublic Is proclaimed l akali be a me a*\ntbe first to offer It my sword.\u201d\n\nand that news material for guidance is\npractically worthless.\nFull of Bargains\nThe market Is \u201cchuck full\u201d of bar\ngains. Dozens of stocks that are nor\nmally appraised as gilt-edged 44 to\nper cent dividend payers, go begging at\n6 to 8 per cent and even bonds continue\ntq work lower under mysterious pressure.\nThe bravest \u201cplungers\u201d rarely risk more\nthan u few hundred shares, where It was\nformerly blocks of 10,000 to 50,000 shares.\nThose who have money are suffering\nfrom confessed fiscal paralysis; those\nwho have light capital (and they are in\noverwhelming majority in the Wall street\ndistrict), are merely thin voiced mem\nbers of the stagnant host and contribute\nI nothing to the sum of gambling or In\nvestment Intelligence. Liquidation for\nNew England account is probably heav\niest, reckoned on the dividend sacrifice\nbasis, and New Haven is not the only\nissue tnat has gone and Is going to a\n\u201cmeal ticket sacrifice.\u201d Tens of millions\nin securities have been sold out to pro\nvide for the current needs of the \u201cpoor.\nInvestor,\u201d (literally ppor), and New Eng\nland Is the chief sufferer thus lar. And\nyet it must be confessed that there are\nfundamental reasons for stock market\nand money market constriction. The\ndown turn haB been foreshadowed for a\nlong time by such \u201cseers\u201d as Jim Hill,\nJacob Schiff, J. B. Forgan and others\nof that class.\nPrevailing Sullenness\nI am at raid i made a nuisance of my\nself by persistent harping on the long\nunrecognized fact that the fight of radi\ncalism against capital would sooner or\nlater take the form of a terribly dan\ngerous agency for the repression of enter\nprise, destruction of values and revolu\ntion of established business institutions,\nbut the dangerous gravity, of the capital,\nto whose activity the material progiess\nof the country of recent years has been\nand Is largely due, is threatened with\nconfiscation, and its owners with con\ndign punishment. Wholesale nervous\nness and actual fear are now in tangi\nble evidence in the giant markets. Hun\ndreds and thousands of men compose a\nlist, of capitalists who will not risk a\ndollar \u201con a chance,\u201d as they put It. A\ncondition of rank apathy has been cre\nated. Prevailing sullenness, that is dis\nheartening in the extreme, rules and\nfrom It there Is no present evidence of\nrecovery.\nWhen Judge Gary said repeatedly\nthat the United States Steel corporation\ncould compete successfully with the\nbest equipped European steel and Iron\nmills regardless of tariffs, nine out of\nten doubted or openly disbelieved the\nclaim. Tbe steady increase in the vol\nume of American exports during the\nlast three years (a large per cent orig\ninating with the so-called Gary trust),\nhas brought about an overwhelming\nchange of opinion. With quotations of\nproduct ruling $3 to $7 per ton lower\nthan they did on top level and \"trust\u2019*\nexportations more than doubled the cu\nrious demanded how the miracle could\nbe done. The explanation was easy and\nIt is no longer concealed. For that\nmatter It was never concealed. The\ncorporation simply went quietly along\n\u201csawing wood and saying nothing.\u201d\nIt had been the custom of the Levia\nthan producer to put back the part of\nsurplus earnings into plant and expan\nsion. In about eight yours over $400,\n000,000 of \u201cvelvet\u201d went back that\nway. About two years ago a change\nof policy was determined upon. It was\ndecided that ther was no longer vital\nneed for further large expenditure of\nearnings in plant and that the owners\n(the 125,000 shareholders) had a right\nto share In the future surplus earnings.\nThe $10,000,000 to $50,000,000 subtracted\nannually from earnings and turned Into\nImprovements and expansions was sud\ndenly diverted to the pockets of the\ngrand army of Individual shareholders.\nThe wonderful annual surplus could be\nspared to the shareholders for a few\nyears without detriment to plant, or\nImpairment to efficiency, and that is\nwhat is being done now.\nIt was merely the legitimate diver\nsion of a large fraction of the net\nearnings into a different channel. By\ncommon consent the United States Steel\ncorporation has $1 to $3.50 per ton the\nbest of competition In home manufac\nture and is proving by the figures of\nthe custom houses on both sides of the\nw\nIn the Packard cars of today is found the\nanswer to the demand of the discriminat\ning public for finality in an automobile.\nLeft Drive\u2014Entrance from either side.\nCentralized Control Board A real\nelectrical outfit that is the final\nanswer in convenience.\nPressure Oiling Meets the require\nments of six cylinders.\nA Self-starter That Starts.\nMagneto Ignition Greatest possible\ninsurance against electrical trouble.\nWhen you drive a Packard you will appreciate\nits points of merit which appeal so strongly to\nexperienced users.\nCHARLES DENEGRE\n1922-24 Avenuo F. Birmingham, Alabama\nLINCOLN HIGHWAY CONTRIBUTOR\nf dAsk the man who owns one\n\"Where Quality\nReigns Supreme\"\nCLOTHES THE WHOLE FAMILY\njjVWith Thanksgiving Only Eleven Days Oil\nK You should call here tomorrow and allow ua to show yos charming Suits and Costumes we have assembled for\nThanksgiving wear\u2014and the many social functions that follow.\n$-?4-95 FOR\n43 EXQUISITE\nt i ,lft TAILORED\n^45-00 SUITS\nWorth in a regular\nA way from $50 to $65\n__\nHERE are several hundred Suits to select from\u2014in\nsuch variety of style that, regardless of the occasion\nfor which a Suit may be desired, you will be able to find\nwhat you seek.\nBroadcloth, Duvetyn, Matelasse. Velvet and all the higher\ngrade materials, in all the popular shades. There being\nmany of the favored copper colored ones in the assortment.\nFur trimmings have been used with excellent effect on\ncollar and cuffs, the same as Suits running as high as $Kj\nto $100.\nThe values in these suits are such as come only occasionally\nand then at the end of the season. We make the offer now\nand give you the benefit of a couple of extra months' wear\nof the garments,\n----s\nCHRISTMAS\nSHOPPING\n;CAN BE DONE\nTO A GREAT\nADVANTAGE\nNOW. OUR\nSTOCKS ARE\nAT THEIR\nSEST\u2014AND\nYOU'LL AVOID\nTHE GREAT\nRUSH THAT\nFOLLOWS\nCLOSER TO\nCHRISTMAS.\nWON'T YOU\nCOME NOW\u2014\nAND PROFIT\nA Special Showing arid Sale cf\nBrassiers, Bust Forms and\nCorset Accessories\nWe place on sale tomorrow 80 dozen Brassieres; made of\nfine quality cambric embroidery and lace edge trim\nmings.\n39c Values Special 25c\n.Beautiful Allover Embroidery Brassieres; made with em\nbroidery insertion front and back. A special purchase of\n100 dozen of these 75c and $1.00 values, enables us to of\nfer them to you\nSpecial at 50c Each\nJunil\u2019orm Hip Reducers; made of Ijfrench elastic, fitted\nand adjusted by our expert.\nJuniper Bust Reducers; of pliable, soft French elastic; ex\npertly fitted.\nComplete line of Bust Forms\u2014priced 50c, 75c to $3.50.\nSanitary Aprons zzzzizzz Dress Shields\n50c to $2.50 _ 25c to 50c\nt\nI Costumes\nf With the winter social season\nswinging into live activity, the mind\npof the society matron and the debu\nI tante naturally reverts to the after\nI noon or dinner dress; the party and\nI dancing frock, and where she can best\nsupply her dress needs. There is\nwhere our service asserts its supe\nH noritv.\nIn a Special Sale Tomorrow\nCOSTUMES and DRESSES\nAT $34.95 to $84.95\nWorth $50.00 Up to $125.00\nOnly a limited few of these\u2014about 75 altogether\n\u2014and only one of a kind. Soft, silken fabrics,\ngold or silver embroidered chiffons, soft crepes,\nbeautiful beyond description, in high colors and\npastel shades, elaborately trimmed in rich laces,\ncrystal beads and seed pearls; all new, shown for\nthe first time tomorrow.\nNovelty Neckwear\u2014Full Christmas\nStock 25c to $18.50\nk----/\nt-\u2014-*\\\nExquisite New Blouses\nAT $5.95, $8.50 and $9.95\nReproductions of French Models That Sold at\n$10.00 to $20.00\nWe will show you in our Blouse Section tomorrow\nfaithful copies made especially for us.\nColored Net Blouses with plaid silk vestee, long\nsleeves and drop shoulders, fluffy frill of lace at\nneck and cuff. Special .$5.95\nCream Net Blouse, Medica collar, drop shoulder,\nlong sleeves; has dainty touches of pink or blue\nribbon trimmings $8.50\nSilk Shadow Lace Blouse: has black net vestee,\nrow of rhinestone brilliants down front of vest.\nSpecial ..$9.95\nNew Shipment Silk Shirts. Special\nat $2.50\nh__/\nBeginning Tomorrow\u2014\nAnd continuing throughout the week, in\norder to stimulate early Fur buying we will\noffer you our entire Fur stock to choose wliat\nyou may at an actual saving of one-third any\nother store\u2019s price.\nFurs bought during this week, if bought for\ngift purposes, Christmas presents or what\nnot, will be stored free of charge until w anted,\nupon payment of a cash deposit.\nBlack Fox Sets from \u25a0..$40.00 up\nBlack Lynx Sets from.$45.00 up\nBrown Marten Sets..... $45.00 up\nArctic White Fox Sets_\u2022 \u2022.$25.00 up\nPointed Fox Sets.$30.00 up\nCivet Cat Sets $45.00 up\nCanadian Mink Sets.$60.00 up\nScotch Mole Sets \u2022.$65.00 up\nPopular Priced Furs\nA wonderful assortment of the season\u2019s best\nFurs, in scarfs or muffs; Belgian Hare, Coney,\nNear Seal, Austrian Squirrel and many other\ndependable Furs\u2014\nAT $4.95 to $9.95\n\nf\nAn Unrivaled Sale\nof New Coats\n2000 COATS 200 STYLES\n$14.95, $19.95. $24.95 $29.95\nWorth in a regular way from\n$20.00 to $35.00\nYou have never seen such variety\nin syles, cloths and colorings\nBroadcloths Chinchillas\nMole, Ural Lamb, Plush,\nZibeline, African Curl\nWool, Velour and Duvetyn\nThe London \u201cSport,\u201d the Scotch Derby, the\n\u201cCountry Club\u201d and other recent styles, in\nsizes for women and misses.\nSilk Hose to match all Suits and Cos\ntumes in the Famous Phoenix, McCal\nlum or Kayser makes at\n75c, $1.00 Up to $5.00\nBuy now for g-ift purposes.\nCLOTHES THE WHOLE FAMILY\nI\nA Most Elaborate Line of Fine Hand\nkerchiefs for Xmas. We are showing\nour full line now to help you make\nearly choice\nAt 10c, 15c, 25c and up to $2.50\nAtlantic, that It can undersell the pro\nducers or England. Germany and other\nEuropean countries in their home mar\nkets. Tho foregoing facts are not now\nnew to the hundreds of thousands of\nmen in the steel trade, but the general\npublic has only a dim inkling of the\ntrue inwardness. The history of tho\ncurrent year shows in black and white\nwhat can he done in the saving of\nmoney, without impairment of efficien\ncy. Not even the desperate determina\ntion of the governmental law depart\nment to ,,bust'\u2022 this particular stool\ntrust and put it out of business, seems\nto seriously disturb tho great souls in\ncommand.\nBargains in Securities\nThere has probably never been so\nmany proved dividend earners on the\nmarket at such low average quotations\nas now adorn the lists. New investors\nare In the market to some extent, but\nthey are not uncountable in numbers or\nresistless in force. They simply buy\nwhen favored specialties look attrac\ntive, but they are seldom inspired with\nactual bullishness. Few of them will\nadmit they anticipate an early upward\nmovement, hut they hold to the theory\nthat prices cannot sink much lower, un\nless the whole country goes to the dogs.\nAdmittedly the United States Is the\nworld and it is hard to recognize the\npossibility of a genuine panic in the\nnear future. Even the most earnest\npreachers of the goepnl of calamity\nhave their limits, and they confess that\nsooner or later they expect a return\nof prosperity and popular serenity. Just\nnow, however, they prefer to feel had.\nThe prophecy la oft heard that money\nwill bo easy after the first of the year,\nand that stocks bought now and held\nstubbornly will yield large speculative\nprofits during the winter months. The\nJanuary distribution of interest and\ndividends will total larger than on any\nprevious date In the country's history,\nso the statisticians say. That perform\nance once over there should be th\u00ab\ngreatest loanable capital ever accumu\nlated In the banks of the republic. It\nis not wholly Improbable that the coun\ntry will be the beneficiary of tremen\ndous fiscal plenty Instead of starving\nfor meager accommodations, as so many\nprofess to fear.\nWall street takes less Interest in\ncurrency legislation than might he Im\nagined. Few know just what the pend\ning .measure aims at. and Just how tho\nbusiness of the country is going to tie\nbenefited by its passage, consequently\noutside of specialists and politicians,\nsmall Interest Is shown in Wasnlngton\nbulletins on that subject. There Is not\nnearly as much excitement over curren\ncy developments as there Is over the\nrevolu'loriary performances smite of\nthe ltlo Grande. The deep sea thinkers\nare framing vvlerd conjectures over the\nInternational influences that a first\nclass row with Mexico would generate.\nAt the moment, though, quotations are\nonly Jumped up and down In nervous\nfractions over the bulletins of unrest.\nBut somehow the war gossip fails to\nproduce either volcanic booms or breaks\nSines John\nQuit Drinking\nBy John's Wile\nl aed Golden Itemedy, The Great Home\nTreatment For Druukarda\nOdorlewM and TaMtleHN\u2014Any Lady Can\nGive It Secretly At Home In Ten,\nCoffee Or Food\nCosts Nothing to Try\nIf you have a huahund. aon. brother, father or\nirtenst wno la a victim of liquoi, all you have to do ia\nto aend your name .ind atldieaa on the coupon n*|.\u00bbw\nYou may be thankful aa long aa you live that you\ndid It.\n\nI\nI\non tho exchange. Currency partisan\nship is confined to limited factions and\nthe spirit of conference seems to be\ngrowing warmer. Friends of the Pres\nident predict a series of conspicuous\npolitical triumphs during the ensuing\nyear.\nThat Obliging Boy\nFrom Pearson\u2019s Weekly.\nWhen Professor Vambery, the famous\nOrientalist, whose death occurred re\ncently, arrived at Sandringham on a\nvisit, he received a message that Queen\nAlexandra wanted to see him.\nHe decided to wash his hands first,\nso he went to his room and rang tho\nbell to ask for some hot water. No\none came, though he rang the bell re\npeatedly.\nThen there came a knock at the door\nand a youth entered. \"Do yftu want\nanything, professor?\" he asked.\n\"Yes,\" replied tho professor, \"I have\nbeen ringing for some hot water.\"\n\"Wait a minute, and I\u2019ll get you\nsome,\" was the obliging reply. The boy\ndisappeared, returning in a few minutes\nwith a large jug of hot water, which\nhe placed on the washstand. The pro\nfessor thanked him. and he withdrew.\nAfter he had washed, the professor\nrlescended to pay his respects to his\nroyal hostess, hut after a few minutes\u2019\nconversation he was surprised to see\nhis \"hot water\" boy come up to the\ngroup.\n\"Ah, professor,\" Queen Alexandra re\nmarked, introducing the boy, \"this is\nmy son!\"\nAfter that the. professor nicknamed\nthe boy, who is now King George V,\n\u201cThe Royal Jug Bearer.\"\nFinds New Indians\nAlbert Lang, whose is exploring the\nsources of the Amazon, for the Brazilian\nogvernment, has Informed F. N. Dellen\nhaugh, secretary of the Explorers\u2019 club,\nof the discovery of a new tribe of In\ndians, 1000 from civilisation, between the\nj headwaters of the Cr\u2019rary and Molu riv\ners. Mr. I.ang gives a picturesque de\nscription of the savages, who, he says,\nJ took him for a god. embracing his feet\nj to show their devotion. Their tools, he\nwrites .are stone, and their ideas so un\nusual us to suggest their belonging to\nanother age. The Jewish east of their\nI features might lead one to infer that they\nv ere of the lost tribes and not their Ig\nI noranee of iron and writing argue against\nit, says the New York Tribune.\n\u201cI am sitting in a m a I oca (hut).\" writes\nMr. Lang, \"of a curious tribe of genuine!\nsavage, arriving here after taking ray\nsix-man canoe above the headwaters of'\nthe Calrary and Moju rivers, fighting our\nway through five dangerous rapids to get\nhere. After 15 days' search 1 got In touch\nwith a virgin tribe, which can be so de\nscribed because they were wholly un\ntouched and unspoiled by civilization\nThey use stone axes and by their aid have\ncleared away some 30 acres of jungle, and\nso blunt are these tools that the trees\nlook as If they had been chewed off.\n\"They grow cotten and go wholly\nnude, only the women wearing waist\nbands. I was received hospitably and\ncarefully watched. They embraced me\nfrequently and gave me bad drinks. I am\nhere to look up the Indigenous tribes for\nthe government of Brazil and ascertain\ntheir possibilities and the beat means of\nentering into relations with them. They\nare like big savage children, kind, but\nsuspicious. Some of the men have He\nbraic features. They show great skill\nwith the bow and arrow, some of the\nformer measuring eight feet.\"\nA Sherlock on the Stage\nMr. Quadratstein, one of the most im\nportant witnesses in the prosecution of\nthe men charged with being concerned\nin the theft of Max Mayer\u2019s famous pearl\nnecklace, again vainly tried to lecture\nat the Folies-Bergere, the Paris music\nhall. Mr. Quadratstein has been engaged\nto tell the public the story of the neck\nlace and his adventures In his amateur\n\".Sherlock Holmes\" work. On the first\nnight he was greeted with a storm of\nhisses and abuse which drove him from\nthe stage, says a Paris cable to the Lon\ndon Chfonicls.\nWhen he arrived on th\u00ab- stage again in\nhis traveling coat and proceeded to take,\nit off before addressing the public, n\nnumber of spectators started a deafening\nnoise with cries of \"Spy! Spy!\" \"Get\nout!*' \"Shut up!\" \"Do you need a penny\nto leave the stage?\nMr. Quadratstein tried vainly to speak,\nand his insistence aroused a violent tu\nmult. Spectators pelted him with to\nmatoes, apples, corks and pennies, while\nall sorts of Insults were shouted at him.\nThe manifestation lasted a quarter of an\nhour, and finished only when Mr. Quad\nratstein left the stage.\nAbolishing the Machine\nFrom the St. Louis Republic.\n\"I understand they have done away\nwith machine politics In your town.\"\n\"They sure have\u2014ever since they fixed\nit so that we had to vote by machinery.\"\nThe Modern <*irl\n\"But are you sure, young man, that\nyou can support my daughter in the style\nIn which she has been accustomed?\n\"Much better, sir. To be frank with\nyou, I rather suspect It to bo one of h#r\nreasons for marrying.\nINDIGESTION; DYSPEPSIA, GAS.\n_ SOUR STOMACH-PAPFS DIAPEPSIN\nTime it! In five minutes\nyour upset stomach\nwill feel fine\nYou don\u2019t want a slow remedy when\nyour stomach Is bad\u2014or an uncertain\none\u2014or a harmful one\u2014your stomach la\ntoo valuable; you mustn\u2019t Injure It with\ndrastic drugs.\nPape\u2019s Dlapepsin is noted for Its\nspeed in giving relief; its harmlessness;\nits certain unfailing action in regulat\ning sick, sour, gassy stomachs. Its\nmillions of cures in indigestion, dyspep-,\nsia, gastritis and other stomach trouble\nhas made it famous the world over.\nKeep this perfect stomach doctor in\nyour home\u2014keep it handy\u2014get a larg\nflfty-eent case from any drug store,\nand then if anyone should eat some\nthing which doesn\u2019t agree with them; If\nwhat they eat lays like lead, ferments\nand sours and forms gas; causes head\nache, dizziness and nausea: eructations\nof acid and undigested food\u2014remember\nas soon as Papes Diapepsin comes In\ncontact with the stomach, all such dis\ntress vanishes. Its promptness, cer\ntainty and ease in overcoming the\nworst stomach disorders is a rsveiation\nti^ those who try It.","height":"27880","width":"19748"}}
